The paper discusses the use of deep reinforcement learning to control an autonomous vehicle in dense traffic scenarios. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given the focus on learning a continuous control policy, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely categories. However, the use of deep learning and simulation-based evaluation also suggests cs.LG and cs.CV as likely categories. Finally, the emphasis on control and decision-making in a dynamic environment points towards cs.SY as a possible category.
